1
00:00:21,320 --> 00:00:26,430
[2009]

2
00:00:29,030 --> 00:00:29,640
Jiang,

3
00:00:30,550 --> 00:00:32,030
go over these two cases.

4
00:00:38,470 --> 00:00:40,350
These days, not many young people

5
00:00:40,350 --> 00:00:41,750
are into pocket watches.

6
00:00:42,620 --> 00:00:44,110
This is quite an antique.

7
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:45,840
Don't stay up too late.

8
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:46,320
Okay.

9
00:02:15,820 --> 00:02:21,540
[Sunsets Secrets Regrets]

10
00:02:21,850 --> 00:02:24,220
[Episode 6]

11
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:28,120
Let me see.

12
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:30,800
What was the name?

13
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:34,079
It was...

14
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:37,430
Li Neng.

15
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:50,190
[Intake Officer: Jiang Cheng,
Fang Hongcheng]

16
00:03:03,690 --> 00:03:04,880
I admit

17
00:03:05,620 --> 00:03:07,480
you've got quite an imagination.

18
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:09,870
But police work relies on evidence.

19
00:03:10,170 --> 00:03:11,570
Do you have any evidence?

20
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:39,490
[To Jiang Cheng]

21
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:31,320
[Jiang Hansheng]

22
00:05:31,430 --> 00:05:32,360
Sorry,

23
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:35,870
the number you dialed
cannot be reached at the moment.

24
00:05:54,510 --> 00:05:56,450
Hello, Criminal Investigation Brigade,
Nancheng Branch.

25
00:05:56,450 --> 00:05:58,250
Hello, is Zhou Jin there?

26
00:05:58,640 --> 00:06:00,690
Zhou Jin? Zhou Jin went home.

27
00:06:01,860 --> 00:06:03,260
Is this Professor Jiang?

28
00:06:04,070 --> 00:06:04,700
Yes.

29
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:07,350
Zhou Jin left a while ago.

30
00:06:07,380 --> 00:06:09,180
Maybe you can try her cell phone.

31
00:06:10,510 --> 00:06:10,950
Okay.

32
00:06:11,510 --> 00:06:12,110
Thank you.

33
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:28,040
Hansheng.

34
00:06:29,390 --> 00:06:30,070
Sir.

35
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:32,500
Do you need anything?

36
00:06:35,159 --> 00:06:36,690
I want to look into someone.

37
00:06:37,270 --> 00:06:38,800
Who do you want to look into?

38
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:41,680
Jiang Cheng.

39
00:06:54,370 --> 00:06:55,170
Where are you?

40
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:57,270
Do you want me to pick you up?

41
00:06:57,270 --> 00:06:58,070
I'm at home.

42
00:06:59,260 --> 00:07:00,040
My own home.

43
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:01,920
I wanted to grab something,

44
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:02,830
so I came back.

45
00:07:04,230 --> 00:07:05,160
Jiang Hansheng.

46
00:07:05,930 --> 00:07:06,480
Okay.

47
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:18,600
Zhou Jin.

48
00:07:19,870 --> 00:07:20,750
Do you like me?

49
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:25,480
I had

50
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,750
a boyfriend

51
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:28,870
for many years.

52
00:07:29,510 --> 00:07:31,240
That was Jiang Cheng, right?

53
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,270
I warned you before,

54
00:07:33,270 --> 00:07:34,930
and I'm telling you again now.

55
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:36,950
Stay away from me.

56
00:07:37,730 --> 00:07:38,320
Zhou Jin.

57
00:07:39,380 --> 00:07:40,380
You lost a button.

58
00:07:43,220 --> 00:07:45,020
I don't even know how it came off.

59
00:07:58,510 --> 00:07:59,440
Why are you here?

60
00:08:02,510 --> 00:08:03,710
Why did you come here?

61
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:06,980
Do you not like living with me?

62
00:08:11,410 --> 00:08:11,940
No.

63
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:14,970
I came back to get some things.

64
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,530
What happened to your face?

65
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:26,220
I was at the playground today.

66
00:08:26,220 --> 00:08:27,360
I was hit by a ball.

67
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,580
Let's go inside first.

68
00:08:39,730 --> 00:08:40,270
Let's go.

69
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:49,970
That's me and my brother.

70
00:08:54,930 --> 00:08:55,640
Have a seat.

71
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:09,600
Watch some TV.

72
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:11,440
I'm gonna pack some things.

73
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,440
I'll be done soon.

74
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:13,510
Then we can

75
00:09:14,170 --> 00:09:15,170
go home together.

76
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:29,210
What...

77
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:31,210
book were you just reading?

78
00:09:32,590 --> 00:09:33,790
The Lord of the Rings.

79
00:09:47,180 --> 00:09:48,230
I'll be quick.

80
00:09:51,610 --> 00:09:52,370
Zhou Jin.

81
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,180
when I married you,

82
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:05,220
was that taking advantage of you?

83
00:10:14,450 --> 00:10:15,380
Of course not.

84
00:10:17,830 --> 00:10:18,880
I married you

85
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,060
because you can hold me up.

86
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:24,920
You make me feel safe.

87
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,030
Zhou Jin.

88
00:10:35,030 --> 00:10:35,840
You can try.

89
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:37,800
Try what?

90
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:41,480
Falling in love with me.

91
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:55,760
Help me move.

92
00:10:56,630 --> 00:10:57,240
Today.

93
00:10:58,390 --> 00:11:00,120
Move everything to your place.

94
00:11:01,460 --> 00:11:02,030
Okay.

95
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:03,760
I'll help you.

96
00:11:32,630 --> 00:11:33,430
What's wrong?

97
00:11:34,150 --> 00:11:35,480
You want to take it back?

98
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:38,760
You can wear it as a necklace.

99
00:11:39,870 --> 00:11:41,260
I run around every day,

100
00:11:41,780 --> 00:11:42,810
what if I lose it?

101
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:50,240
Whatever you say.

102
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:51,720
Whatever you say.

103
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:06,660
[Dan]

104
00:12:10,670 --> 00:12:11,270
Dan.

105
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:12,390
Zhou Jin,

106
00:12:12,790 --> 00:12:14,320
you're getting suspended.

107
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:15,590
Why?

108
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,530
On what grounds?

109
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:20,720
There's a last-minute meeting today.

110
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:21,720
In the meeting,

111
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:24,240
they said during your interrogation
of Lai Zhengtian,

112
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:25,040
you engaged in

113
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:25,870
suggestive questioning,

114
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:27,930
and you coerced him into confessing.

115
00:12:28,150 --> 00:12:31,000
As for whether Lai Zhengtian
filed the complaint himself,

116
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,320
or someone from the inside reported it,

117
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:33,550
we don't know yet.

118
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:35,670
But I have to say,

119
00:12:35,670 --> 00:12:37,080
Chief Tan is really reliable.

120
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:38,240
As soon as this happened,

121
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:39,390
he went straight to the bureau,

122
00:12:39,390 --> 00:12:42,100
saying it was him
who let you join the interrogation,

123
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:43,730
and that the responsibility lies with him.

124
00:12:43,730 --> 00:12:44,480
But the problem is,

125
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,340
I didn't violate any rules at all.

126
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:48,040
Wasn't there a video recording?

127
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:49,640
They can see it very clearly.

128
00:12:50,030 --> 00:12:51,510
Yes, very clearly.

129
00:12:51,510 --> 00:12:53,260
You were too close to Lai Zhengtian.

130
00:12:53,260 --> 00:12:54,750
It was both
against regulations and dangerous.

131
00:12:54,750 --> 00:12:56,030
And you ended up getting hurt.

132
00:12:56,030 --> 00:12:57,600
Anyway, the decision is

133
00:12:57,780 --> 00:12:58,980
to suspend your work.

134
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:00,600
As for the penalty,

135
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:03,610
we'll have to wait
for the official results.

136
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,200
For how many days?

137
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:07,030
It depends on how they classify it.

138
00:13:07,030 --> 00:13:08,430
Just wait for the notice.

139
00:13:09,030 --> 00:13:10,230
Is this a suspension?

140
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:12,250
More like being taken off work.

141
00:13:12,580 --> 00:13:13,150
Alright.

142
00:13:13,450 --> 00:13:14,340
I got it.

143
00:13:30,270 --> 00:13:31,130
What happened?

144
00:13:33,460 --> 00:13:34,920
They've taken me off work.

145
00:13:35,780 --> 00:13:37,980
And I have to undergo an investigation.

146
00:13:39,870 --> 00:13:40,670
It's fine.

147
00:13:41,420 --> 00:13:42,950
My salary is pretty decent.

148
00:13:45,940 --> 00:13:47,150
Is that the point?

149
00:13:54,060 --> 00:13:55,260
You're pretty lucky.

150
00:13:55,830 --> 00:13:57,250
I'm not high-maintenance.

151
00:13:57,250 --> 00:13:58,580
I'm easy to take care of.

152
00:14:00,870 --> 00:14:01,750
I'm so lucky.

153
00:14:43,920 --> 00:14:44,790
Cheng is here.

154
00:14:45,710 --> 00:14:46,590
Cheng.

155
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,510
How's that thing going, Cheng?

156
00:14:49,510 --> 00:14:51,510
Don't ask questions you shouldn't.

157
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:53,550
It's handled.

158
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:54,960
Here.

159
00:14:54,980 --> 00:14:56,060
Cheng, cheers.

160
00:15:49,390 --> 00:15:49,960
Liu.

161
00:16:07,470 --> 00:16:08,040
Come in.

162
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:16,290
Leader Yao has arrived.

163
00:16:16,620 --> 00:16:18,480
He is in the task force office now.

164
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:19,760
I see.

165
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:22,260
You guys are close, right?

166
00:16:23,310 --> 00:16:23,910
We've met.

167
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:28,360
You were at the
Provincial Crime Research Office before.

168
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:31,270
You must have handled many major cases
with him.

169
00:16:31,670 --> 00:16:32,800
I'll head over then.

170
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:34,210
Okay, you go ahead.

171
00:16:34,290 --> 00:16:35,750
Thanks for your hard work.

172
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:49,760
The new boss has just taken over,

173
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:51,880
and he's kicking you out.

174
00:16:54,160 --> 00:16:54,830
Sir.

175
00:16:55,670 --> 00:16:57,340
Don't kick me while I'm down.

176
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,670
To tell you the truth,

177
00:17:01,150 --> 00:17:03,150
it was Leader Yao

178
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:06,410
who fully supported you
to take on the Meng Ling case.

179
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:08,280
Look at what you've done now.

180
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:10,010
It's like a slap in his face.

181
00:17:11,270 --> 00:17:12,200
He knows me?

182
00:17:12,349 --> 00:17:13,700
Of course he does.

183
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:15,800
He handled the 8.17 Case

184
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:17,380
himself.

185
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:25,550
[Task Force]

186
00:17:23,750 --> 00:17:24,310
Come in.

187
00:17:29,990 --> 00:17:34,530
[Yao Weihai,
the leader of 8.17 task force]

188
00:17:32,750 --> 00:17:33,720
It's really you.

189
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:36,410
Leader Yao.

190
00:17:37,030 --> 00:17:37,890
Close the door.

191
00:17:48,930 --> 00:17:49,510
How is it?

192
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:51,430
Are you getting used to it here?

193
00:17:51,970 --> 00:17:52,700
Pretty good.

194
00:17:54,020 --> 00:17:54,650
Hansheng,

195
00:17:55,320 --> 00:17:57,250
Mr. Wang went through a lot of trouble

196
00:17:57,250 --> 00:17:59,390
to get you that teaching job
at the University

197
00:17:59,390 --> 00:18:00,760
just to keep you safe.

198
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:02,610
But you insist

199
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:04,500
on getting involved in this case.

200
00:18:05,370 --> 00:18:07,830
Have you thought about
how big the risks are?

201
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:09,700
Hiding

202
00:18:10,170 --> 00:18:11,430
is never the solution.

203
00:18:14,170 --> 00:18:15,900
If I hadn't come back this time,

204
00:18:16,380 --> 00:18:17,300
I would have never known

205
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:18,720
you'd been at the Provincial Department

206
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:20,130
the whole time.

207
00:18:21,620 --> 00:18:23,480
If you hadn't come back this time,

208
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:25,090
I would have never known

209
00:18:25,340 --> 00:18:28,400
that you'd been investigating
the 8.17 Case all along.

210
00:18:32,860 --> 00:18:34,180
Mr. Wang was right.

211
00:18:34,860 --> 00:18:35,790
There's a kind of

212
00:18:35,830 --> 00:18:37,690
restrained ruthlessness in you.

213
00:18:38,790 --> 00:18:40,450
And that kind of ruthlessness

214
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:43,580
makes people feel uneasy.

215
00:18:44,930 --> 00:18:45,930
Does Zhou Jin know

216
00:18:46,230 --> 00:18:48,020
that you are still a police officer

217
00:18:48,020 --> 00:18:50,110
of the Criminal Investigation Department,

218
00:18:50,110 --> 00:18:51,110
Professor Jiang?

219
00:18:52,720 --> 00:18:53,590
In Haizhou,

220
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:55,420
only a few core members

221
00:18:56,220 --> 00:18:57,200
of the public security bureau

222
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:58,660
know about this identity.

223
00:18:59,290 --> 00:19:00,890
Zhou Jin is not a core member.

224
00:19:01,310 --> 00:19:02,110
Is it possible

225
00:19:02,510 --> 00:19:03,580
that Leader Yao doesn't want me

226
00:19:03,580 --> 00:19:04,510
on the 8.17 case?

227
00:19:04,750 --> 00:19:06,310
No, why wouldn't he want me?

228
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:07,920
Perhaps,

229
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:10,140
I'm too eager to solve the case,

230
00:19:10,140 --> 00:19:11,070
or

231
00:19:11,300 --> 00:19:12,080
I'm not qualified enough,

232
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:13,110
or I don't carry enough weight,

233
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:14,510
or I'd let personal feelings get involved.

234
00:19:14,510 --> 00:19:16,130
Alright, stop guessing.

235
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:17,590
He's a high-ranking leader.

236
00:19:17,590 --> 00:19:20,190
He doesn't have time
to think about you all day.

237
00:19:21,090 --> 00:19:22,420
Just go back and behave.

238
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,110
Study that

239
00:19:24,510 --> 00:19:26,430
interrogation record carefully,

240
00:19:26,430 --> 00:19:27,830
and reflect on yourself.

241
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:29,160
Sir,

242
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:30,910
I don't want to be suspended.

243
00:19:30,910 --> 00:19:33,110
There are lots of things you don't want.

244
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:35,860
Does it make a difference?

245
00:19:37,370 --> 00:19:37,900
Alright.

246
00:19:39,630 --> 00:19:40,450
It's almost

247
00:19:41,710 --> 00:19:43,180
August 17th.

248
00:19:44,070 --> 00:19:45,370
If you don't ask for leave,

249
00:19:45,370 --> 00:19:46,700
I'll approve it myself.

250
00:19:47,260 --> 00:19:48,990
Go back and visit your parents.

251
00:19:55,790 --> 00:19:56,850
I'll head out then.

252
00:20:01,750 --> 00:20:03,750
The situation is still unclear.

253
00:20:04,050 --> 00:20:05,600
For the sake of your safety,

254
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:10,090
I don't want you involved in this case.

255
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:11,570
If Mr. Wang

256
00:20:11,790 --> 00:20:12,400
knew,

257
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:14,140
he would agree with me.

258
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,460
Zhou Jin's suspension

259
00:20:20,110 --> 00:20:21,910
was also arranged by you, right?

260
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:25,820
You are the head of the task force.

261
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,920
I believe whatever you decide,

262
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:29,560
you've got your reasons.

263
00:20:30,070 --> 00:20:31,800
But I also want to say something

264
00:20:31,830 --> 00:20:33,360
about my partner, Zhou Jin.

265
00:20:34,030 --> 00:20:35,110
Her ability

266
00:20:35,350 --> 00:20:36,590
got her into the CIB

267
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:38,690
and onto the Meng Ling case.

268
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:44,790
If it weren't for the major breakthrough

269
00:20:44,790 --> 00:20:45,880
in the 8.17 case,

270
00:20:46,510 --> 00:20:48,510
I believe you wouldn't have come back.

271
00:20:48,510 --> 00:20:50,310
However, before your next move,

272
00:20:51,030 --> 00:20:51,960
there is someone

273
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,270
I think you should pay attention to.

274
00:20:54,270 --> 00:20:54,680
Who?

275
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,130
Jiang Cheng.

276
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:57,510
Why?

277
00:20:59,590 --> 00:21:01,350
Aren't you supposed to ask
who he is first?

278
00:21:01,350 --> 00:21:02,680
I've checked the files.

279
00:21:03,030 --> 00:21:04,350
He's He Wu's subordinate.

280
00:21:04,350 --> 00:21:05,550
He used to be a cop too.

281
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:06,560
That's it.

282
00:21:09,380 --> 00:21:10,640
I think that's enough.

283
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:19,730
How did it go?

284
00:21:20,070 --> 00:21:20,870
Done talking?

285
00:21:22,350 --> 00:21:23,200
I'm screwed.

286
00:21:23,860 --> 00:21:25,190
I really got suspended.

287
00:21:26,180 --> 00:21:27,510
You only got suspended.

288
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:29,030
I was fired to my face.

289
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:32,740
They won't let me assist
in the investigation anymore.

290
00:21:33,510 --> 00:21:34,570
What's the reason?

291
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:43,440
It seems like ever since you married me,

292
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:45,600
nothing good has happened to you.

293
00:21:50,830 --> 00:21:51,680
Marrying you

294
00:21:52,830 --> 00:21:55,760
is already the best thing
that's ever happened to me.

295
00:22:04,310 --> 00:22:05,170
Of course it is.

296
00:22:11,230 --> 00:22:13,360
Meng Ling's case is about to be closed.

297
00:22:13,690 --> 00:22:15,890
Chief Tan said he could give me time off.

298
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:18,110
I want to go home to see my parents.

299
00:22:18,110 --> 00:22:19,310
Will you come with me?

300
00:22:20,570 --> 00:22:21,500
I'll go with you.

301
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:27,900
But the leverage Meng Ling has

302
00:22:28,270 --> 00:22:29,590
over Lai San

303
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:31,240
still remains unknown.

304
00:22:33,310 --> 00:22:34,160
And that gun.

305
00:22:36,180 --> 00:22:37,310
It's still missing.

306
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:41,970
Everything will become clear.

307
00:23:23,120 --> 00:23:23,720
Mr. Jiang,

308
00:23:24,220 --> 00:23:24,750
please.

309
00:23:38,620 --> 00:23:39,350
You're here.

310
00:23:40,350 --> 00:23:40,750
Boss.

311
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:42,330
Cheng.

312
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:44,750
Ms. Qiu.

313
00:23:46,550 --> 00:23:47,110
Hello.

314
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:48,040
I'm Qiu Ye.

315
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:50,530
Hello. I'm Jiang Cheng.

316
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:57,140
Don't you remember me,

317
00:23:57,660 --> 00:23:58,520
Officer Jiang?

318
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:09,190
[2011]

319
00:24:04,470 --> 00:24:05,060
Freeze.

320
00:24:05,080 --> 00:24:05,850
Police.

321
00:24:06,030 --> 00:24:07,270
Don't move.

322
00:24:09,750 --> 00:24:10,350
Freeze.

323
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,030
Hold them all down.

324
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:21,030
Stand up.

325
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:24,790
Stand up!

326
00:24:59,110 --> 00:25:00,440
Will I go to jail,

327
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:01,550
Officer?

328
00:25:01,830 --> 00:25:02,690
Pregnant women

329
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:04,750
usually serve their sentence
outside of prison.

330
00:25:04,750 --> 00:25:05,950
Don't touch it again.

331
00:25:06,310 --> 00:25:07,720
If not for yourself,

332
00:25:08,160 --> 00:25:09,960
do it for the child in your belly.

333
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:17,840
It seems Officer Jiang still remembers me.

334
00:25:19,790 --> 00:25:20,550
Don't swear.

335
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:21,700
Just call me Cheng.

336
00:25:22,450 --> 00:25:23,110
Okay.

337
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:26,080
I haven't seen you in years,

338
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:26,800
Ms...

339
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:27,790
Qiu.

340
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:29,690
You are still so beautiful.

341
00:25:30,560 --> 00:25:33,160
I've spent a lot of money
on my face these years.

342
00:25:33,880 --> 00:25:34,680
It's worth it.

343
00:25:34,790 --> 00:25:35,270
Really?

344
00:25:36,730 --> 00:25:38,000
Here, let's sit.

345
00:25:48,270 --> 00:25:48,960
Cheng,

346
00:25:49,790 --> 00:25:51,550
Lai Zhengtian is finished.

347
00:25:53,070 --> 00:25:54,000
I said

348
00:25:54,930 --> 00:25:56,390
I'd let you take his place,

349
00:25:57,070 --> 00:25:58,270
and I'll keep my word.

350
00:25:58,750 --> 00:25:59,810
From now on, Ms. Qiu

351
00:26:00,070 --> 00:26:01,070
is your resource.

352
00:26:06,270 --> 00:26:07,960
I wonder which part of the resources

353
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:09,490
is Ms. Qiu responsible for?

354
00:26:11,350 --> 00:26:12,610
The unspeakable part.

355
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:16,200
Boss,

356
00:26:16,810 --> 00:26:19,270
does that mean
I'm really entering the core?

357
00:26:19,790 --> 00:26:20,390
Of course.

358
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:21,370
Absolutely.

359
00:26:26,070 --> 00:26:26,720
Ms. Qiu,

360
00:26:27,060 --> 00:26:29,260
I'll be counting on you then from now on.

361
00:26:30,350 --> 00:26:32,010
Don't get all polite just yet.

362
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:35,200
There's something
I haven't had a chance to say yet.

363
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:35,790
Boss He,

364
00:26:36,750 --> 00:26:39,350
you know the guns
that slipped from your hand?

365
00:26:39,650 --> 00:26:41,340
Old Scorpion isn't happy about that.

366
00:26:41,340 --> 00:26:43,200
That's why he sent me here

367
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:45,550
to talk it over with you.

368
00:26:47,350 --> 00:26:48,280
What do you mean?

369
00:26:49,510 --> 00:26:51,320
The Hengyun Logistics channel

370
00:26:51,350 --> 00:26:52,950
will be shut down for a while.

371
00:26:53,490 --> 00:26:54,490
And all inventory

372
00:26:56,180 --> 00:26:57,180
will be recalled.

373
00:26:58,640 --> 00:26:59,750
When will it start?

374
00:27:06,440 --> 00:27:07,070
Now.

375
00:27:10,790 --> 00:27:11,450
The power's out!

376
00:27:11,450 --> 00:27:13,110
Go check the circuit breaker!

377
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:19,790
Old Scorpion says

378
00:27:19,790 --> 00:27:21,920
he wants you to take a break for a while.

379
00:27:27,370 --> 00:27:28,500
Didn't you hear her?

380
00:27:29,590 --> 00:27:31,250
This comes from Old Scorpion.

381
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:40,520
Thank you.

382
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:44,240
If there's nothing else,
I'll be leaving then.

383
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:51,550
Ms. Qiu.

384
00:27:59,030 --> 00:28:01,090
Please go back and tell Old Scorpion.

385
00:28:02,270 --> 00:28:03,240
No matter what,

386
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:06,920
Haizhou still belongs to the He family.

387
00:28:09,150 --> 00:28:11,080
I'll make sure he gets the message.

388
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:40,680
Where are we?

389
00:28:42,550 --> 00:28:43,680
Just got off the highway.

390
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:44,880
There's still half an hour.

391
00:28:44,880 --> 00:28:46,410
You can get some more sleep.

392
00:28:49,930 --> 00:28:51,790
Do you want me to drive for a while?

393
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:52,800
I'm not tired.

394
00:28:58,110 --> 00:28:58,920
What's wrong?

395
00:29:04,270 --> 00:29:05,530
For the last few years,

396
00:29:06,650 --> 00:29:08,650
whenever August 17th comes around,

397
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:10,640
I come back.

398
00:29:12,590 --> 00:29:14,110
Always by myself.

399
00:29:14,830 --> 00:29:15,830
Walking this road

400
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:17,640
alone.

401
00:29:20,200 --> 00:29:22,200
To be honest, I always feel a bit down

402
00:29:23,350 --> 00:29:24,590
around this time.

403
00:29:27,880 --> 00:29:29,480
You got suspended this year.

404
00:29:29,590 --> 00:29:31,120
Doesn't that make it worse?

405
00:29:31,790 --> 00:29:32,470
No.

406
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:35,600
Because you're here with me.

407
00:29:39,550 --> 00:29:40,420
If we get home early,

408
00:29:40,420 --> 00:29:41,880
we can stay a few more days.

409
00:29:49,550 --> 00:29:50,590
Professor Jiang,

410
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:52,550
you're quite good-looking.

411
00:29:55,110 --> 00:29:56,920
Did you marry me for my looks?

412
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:00,920
Don't ask.

413
00:30:32,310 --> 00:30:34,480
I haven't been back to Zhizi Alley
in a long time.

414
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:35,610
It's good to be back.

415
00:30:36,500 --> 00:30:38,030
After you moved away for high school,

416
00:30:38,030 --> 00:30:39,560
you never came back, right?

417
00:30:55,310 --> 00:30:56,400
There's an old man

418
00:30:57,270 --> 00:30:59,000
living in the Courtyard 23 now.

419
00:31:11,720 --> 00:31:12,590
Jin,

420
00:31:12,790 --> 00:31:14,160
you're back quite early this year.

421
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:14,720
Bin,

422
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:15,800
how many times have I told you?

423
00:31:15,800 --> 00:31:17,720
Don't ride that beat-up bike
around my alley.

424
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:18,850
What beat-up bike?

425
00:31:19,270 --> 00:31:20,830
This is a a brand-name one, okay?

426
00:31:20,830 --> 00:31:23,690
People would steal its wheels
if I leave it outside.

427
00:31:24,520 --> 00:31:26,270
[Yan Bin,
the owner of Mr. Yan's hotpot restaurant]

428
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:26,100
Who's this?

429
00:31:26,590 --> 00:31:27,550
He's...

430
00:31:28,310 --> 00:31:29,270
Look who's back!

431
00:31:29,270 --> 00:31:30,070
Mom.

432
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:33,310
My precious daughter.

433
00:31:34,170 --> 00:31:35,760
I missed you.

434
00:31:37,240 --> 00:31:39,040
Why have you lost so much weight?

435
00:31:39,410 --> 00:31:41,310
You need to eat well,
no matter how busy you are.

436
00:31:41,310 --> 00:31:43,370
Your little body
can't take the strain anymore.

437
00:31:43,370 --> 00:31:44,520
I'm fine, really.

438
00:31:46,330 --> 00:31:47,520
Dad, is your leg better?

439
00:31:47,520 --> 00:31:48,430
Same as always.

440
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:51,210
You've got more white hair.

441
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:52,790
All my old friends

442
00:31:52,820 --> 00:31:54,480
have more white hair than I do.

443
00:31:55,550 --> 00:31:56,270
Hansheng,

444
00:31:56,420 --> 00:31:57,420
you must be tired.

445
00:31:57,960 --> 00:31:58,820
Not at all, Mom.

446
00:31:59,590 --> 00:32:00,310
Come in.

447
00:32:00,350 --> 00:32:01,210
Come in and sit.

448
00:32:01,240 --> 00:32:01,720
Right.

449
00:32:01,740 --> 00:32:02,260
I got it.

450
00:32:02,290 --> 00:32:03,030
I got it.

451
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:06,200
Let's go in first.

452
00:32:06,550 --> 00:32:07,810
Bin, come on in with us.

453
00:32:08,790 --> 00:32:09,880
Nah, it's okay, Uncle.

454
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:11,480
I just want to have a word with Jin.

455
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:12,590
Sure. You two chat.

456
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:14,640
Go ahead.

457
00:32:16,070 --> 00:32:17,270
You have a boyfriend?

458
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:19,610
Tomorrow night, dinner time,

459
00:32:19,610 --> 00:32:20,480
we'll talk about it in detail then.

460
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:21,860
Alright? I'm heading off now.

461
00:32:21,860 --> 00:32:22,860
Wait, wait, wait.

462
00:32:23,510 --> 00:32:25,000
Why does he look familiar?

463
00:32:28,060 --> 00:32:30,060
The young master from Courtyard 23?

464
00:32:31,790 --> 00:32:32,990
Right, right, right.

465
00:32:33,690 --> 00:32:34,720
Wait, wait, wait.

466
00:32:36,110 --> 00:32:36,830
Buns, buns.

467
00:32:37,180 --> 00:32:37,580
Buns.

468
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:39,660
My mom told me to bring you these buns.

469
00:32:39,750 --> 00:32:40,830
Here.

470
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:42,470
Is it stuffed
with preserved mustard greens?

471
00:32:42,470 --> 00:32:44,030
Just eat. Who cares what's inside?

472
00:32:44,030 --> 00:32:44,590
Mom.

473
00:32:45,830 --> 00:32:46,920
Buns.

474
00:32:56,850 --> 00:32:57,640
Brother.

475
00:32:58,400 --> 00:32:59,200
Jin has a boyfriend.

476
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:00,460
Do you know about this?

477
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:01,920
Here.

478
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:02,730
Son-in-law,

479
00:33:03,070 --> 00:33:04,340
have another sip with me.

480
00:33:04,340 --> 00:33:05,350
Here's to you, Dad.

481
00:33:05,350 --> 00:33:05,880
Okay.

482
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:12,480
It's been a long time

483
00:33:12,480 --> 00:33:14,270
since I had a drink this good.

484
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:16,730
Come on, eat.

485
00:33:17,050 --> 00:33:18,660
Your mom's cooking is really good.

486
00:33:18,660 --> 00:33:19,590
It's delicious.

487
00:33:22,350 --> 00:33:22,960
Mom,

488
00:33:23,310 --> 00:33:24,680
what are you looking at?

489
00:33:24,880 --> 00:33:25,920
Your mom is looking at her son-in-law.

490
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:28,250
The more she looks,
the more she likes him.

491
00:33:29,190 --> 00:33:30,130
You silly girl,

492
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:31,440
you're really lucky.

493
00:33:32,550 --> 00:33:33,750
Hansheng, this is your first time here.

494
00:33:33,750 --> 00:33:35,550
Let me know if you need anything.

495
00:33:36,070 --> 00:33:37,470
Everything's fine, Mom.

496
00:33:38,160 --> 00:33:38,830
Hansheng,

497
00:33:38,830 --> 00:33:39,830
you don't have to peel them for me.

498
00:33:39,830 --> 00:33:40,920
I can do it myself.

499
00:33:41,340 --> 00:33:41,820
Here.

500
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:45,860
By the way, Mom.

501
00:33:46,310 --> 00:33:47,200
Hansheng

502
00:33:47,240 --> 00:33:49,300
is used to using serving chopsticks.

503
00:33:49,390 --> 00:33:50,020
Okay, okay.

504
00:33:50,020 --> 00:33:50,750
No need, Mom.

505
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,800
There's no need for that at home.

506
00:33:55,590 --> 00:33:57,640
Hansheng has been to our house before,

507
00:33:57,640 --> 00:33:58,310
right?

508
00:33:59,510 --> 00:34:00,110
Has he?

509
00:34:00,680 --> 00:34:01,640
Do you remember?

510
00:34:02,240 --> 00:34:03,880
When Jin was little,

511
00:34:03,900 --> 00:34:05,430
she brought Hansheng home.

512
00:34:05,680 --> 00:34:06,400
I remember.

513
00:34:06,880 --> 00:34:09,080
The two little kids were holding hands.

514
00:34:10,590 --> 00:34:11,800
When did that happen?

515
00:34:12,710 --> 00:34:13,639
Do you remember?

516
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:17,030
What I remember most is that woman.

517
00:34:17,520 --> 00:34:18,980
The nanny from your house.

518
00:34:19,020 --> 00:34:21,550
She was taking care of you
and a few other kids.

519
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:23,520
You were all victims.

520
00:34:23,820 --> 00:34:25,230
Later, she got arrested,

521
00:34:25,250 --> 00:34:27,190
and spent two or three years in prison.

522
00:34:27,190 --> 00:34:28,190
Nanny?

523
00:34:28,590 --> 00:34:29,670
Arrested?

524
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:32,880
You were the one
who first found out about it.

525
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:34,880
And then you brought Hansheng here.

526
00:34:35,710 --> 00:34:37,030
It's normal she doesn't remember.

527
00:34:37,030 --> 00:34:38,940
Back then,
she was always bringing people home.

528
00:34:38,940 --> 00:34:39,830
We were so busy.

529
00:34:39,860 --> 00:34:40,880
Dad, what are you talking about?

530
00:34:40,880 --> 00:34:42,940
Who was always bringing people home?

531
00:34:43,590 --> 00:34:45,840
Maybe it was that fever.

532
00:34:46,219 --> 00:34:47,150
It fried her brain.

533
00:34:47,150 --> 00:34:48,070
So she lost her memory.

534
00:34:48,070 --> 00:34:49,280
What are you talking about?

535
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:50,320
It's true.

536
00:34:50,659 --> 00:34:52,920
That night,
I told her to go home with you.

537
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:54,510
But she wouldn't let go of me.

538
00:34:54,510 --> 00:34:56,590
She insisted on going to find him
in the rain.

539
00:34:56,590 --> 00:34:59,070
Then she got soaked
and came down with a fever the next day.

540
00:34:59,070 --> 00:35:00,070
She was all dazed.

541
00:35:00,320 --> 00:35:01,110
That's true.

542
00:35:02,270 --> 00:35:03,460
Do you remember now?

543
00:35:04,990 --> 00:35:06,150
How old was I?

544
00:35:06,470 --> 00:35:07,730
When you were in elementary school.

545
00:35:07,730 --> 00:35:09,060
You were only this tall.

546
00:35:09,290 --> 00:35:10,420
Elementary school?

547
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:14,810
Do you really remember?

548
00:35:16,530 --> 00:35:18,860
You even wanted
to steal a meatball for me.

549
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:32,740
[1997]

550
00:35:28,210 --> 00:35:29,870
Do you want some shrimp chips?

551
00:35:35,570 --> 00:35:37,050
They're so good.

552
00:35:41,870 --> 00:35:43,430
You don't like them?

553
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:47,830
My mom said

554
00:35:48,800 --> 00:35:50,730
I can't have snacks before dinner.

555
00:35:52,020 --> 00:35:53,080
Aren't you hungry?

556
00:35:58,850 --> 00:36:00,750
Wait here,
I'll steal a big meatball for you.

557
00:36:00,750 --> 00:36:02,210
Meatballs aren't snacks.

558
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:29,800
Here, drink some tea.

559
00:36:51,030 --> 00:36:51,760
Hansheng,

560
00:36:53,720 --> 00:36:54,680
thank you.

561
00:36:57,880 --> 00:36:58,510
Dad,

562
00:36:59,250 --> 00:37:00,650
I should be thanking you.

563
00:37:03,840 --> 00:37:05,170
You finally brought him home.

564
00:37:05,170 --> 00:37:06,740
I'm finally relieved.

565
00:37:08,110 --> 00:37:09,370
Are you happy with him?

566
00:37:09,590 --> 00:37:11,520
What matters is that you're happy.

567
00:37:12,590 --> 00:37:13,510
Back then,

568
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:15,400
it was so hard

569
00:37:15,510 --> 00:37:17,310
to get you to go on a date with him.

570
00:37:20,190 --> 00:37:20,710
Look,

571
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:23,660
he's got a lot to talk about
with your dad.

572
00:37:25,150 --> 00:37:27,010
He teaches Criminal Psychology.

573
00:37:27,190 --> 00:37:29,450
He's very popular with old cops like Dad.

574
00:37:30,760 --> 00:37:31,510
Jin.

575
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:32,920
Busy as you are,

576
00:37:33,030 --> 00:37:34,960
you still need to have a wedding.

577
00:37:36,320 --> 00:37:39,180
You can't keep making Hansheng
compromise for you.

578
00:37:40,050 --> 00:37:42,650
Let's just get through
this busy period first.

579
00:37:43,590 --> 00:37:45,030
For the wedding,

580
00:37:45,110 --> 00:37:47,440
you need to notify the parents and elders.

581
00:37:47,790 --> 00:37:49,300
You can't just decide on your own.

582
00:37:49,300 --> 00:37:50,900
I know. We will.

583
00:37:57,130 --> 00:37:58,930
If your brother were still here,

584
00:37:59,400 --> 00:38:01,260
he'd definitely be happy for you.

585
00:38:05,550 --> 00:38:06,920
He definitely would be.

586
00:38:57,870 --> 00:39:03,350
♪ Win like this, lose like this ♪

587
00:39:03,380 --> 00:39:07,350
♪ Don't mock others' greed and obsession ♪

588
00:39:08,310 --> 00:39:11,750
♪ Grievances and joys are hard to let go ♪

589
00:39:11,770 --> 00:39:13,920
♪ Between heaven and earth ♪

590
00:39:13,940 --> 00:39:16,890
♪ Carefree like this ♪

591
00:39:16,920 --> 00:39:18,430
♪ In a snap of fingers ♪

592
00:39:18,450 --> 00:39:22,800
♪ Time passes like this ♪

593
00:39:22,820 --> 00:39:26,730
♪ You're like this, I'm like this ♪

594
00:39:27,470 --> 00:39:31,110
♪ A sword in hand and a ruler in heart ♪

595
00:39:31,140 --> 00:39:36,270
♪ Let go of ego and place the chess ♪

596
00:39:36,300 --> 00:39:39,060
♪ Dancing with the sword ♪

597
00:39:39,090 --> 00:39:41,460
♪ Writing with the brush ♪

598
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:43,880
♪ In the unseen ♪

599
00:39:43,900 --> 00:39:46,050
♪ Each one has his own gift ♪

600
00:39:56,070 --> 00:39:56,920
This is?

601
00:39:58,780 --> 00:39:59,910
This is my brother's

602
00:40:00,870 --> 00:40:02,100
favorite song.

603
00:40:04,670 --> 00:40:05,550
Those...

604
00:40:06,580 --> 00:40:09,180
are all the cassettes
my brother bought for me.

605
00:40:10,220 --> 00:40:11,300
People these days

606
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:15,200
don't seem to listen to cassettes anymore.

607
00:40:17,510 --> 00:40:20,590
Cassettes feel so old-fashioned.

608
00:40:22,840 --> 00:40:25,100
It's like some things from my childhood.

609
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:29,030
They feel so far away.

610
00:40:30,360 --> 00:40:32,550
I don't even seem to remember them.

611
00:40:33,880 --> 00:40:35,360
But there are others

612
00:40:38,480 --> 00:40:39,960
I remember very clearly.

613
00:40:41,920 --> 00:40:43,850
And when I think of them sometimes,

614
00:40:44,760 --> 00:40:46,070
I feel a little sad.

615
00:40:49,030 --> 00:40:50,630
Jiang Hansheng, do you know?

616
00:40:52,030 --> 00:40:53,150
Actually,

617
00:40:56,500 --> 00:40:57,500
Zhizi Alley

618
00:40:58,260 --> 00:41:00,140
is a place I'm afraid of.

619
00:41:02,060 --> 00:41:03,520
I really want to come back,

620
00:41:05,910 --> 00:41:07,200
but I'm so scared.

621
00:41:17,710 --> 00:41:19,070
If I take one more step,

622
00:41:20,010 --> 00:41:22,810
I'll be the farthest away
from home I've ever been.

623
00:41:25,030 --> 00:41:26,890
It's from "The Lord of the Rings."

624
00:41:29,570 --> 00:41:31,300
As long as the case gets solved,

625
00:41:32,670 --> 00:41:34,130
I don't care how many steps

626
00:41:34,670 --> 00:41:35,550
I have to take.

627
00:41:37,670 --> 00:41:38,710
I'm just afraid

628
00:41:40,670 --> 00:41:42,110
I won't have the chance.

629
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:44,710
You will.

630
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:52,700
What song do you want to listen to?

631
00:41:52,770 --> 00:41:53,900
I'll play it for you.

632
00:41:55,460 --> 00:41:57,060
I like songs without lyrics.

633
00:41:59,320 --> 00:42:00,720
Lyrics disturb the mind.

634
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:03,060
They create strong
psychological suggestions,

635
00:42:03,060 --> 00:42:05,190
or even self-fulfilling prophecies.

636
00:42:09,480 --> 00:42:10,410
Am I being weird?

637
00:42:14,360 --> 00:42:16,420
You lived next door when we were kids.

638
00:42:17,420 --> 00:42:18,340
Why

639
00:42:19,800 --> 00:42:21,330
didn't I ever play with you?

640
00:42:23,530 --> 00:42:25,050
Maybe because I was weird.

641
00:42:26,180 --> 00:42:28,380
Being weird means you're interesting.

642
00:42:28,570 --> 00:42:30,230
I was the one who didn't get it.

643
00:42:31,860 --> 00:42:32,900
I'm sorry.

644
00:42:33,230 --> 00:42:35,510
The bed here isn't as big
as the one at our home.

645
00:42:35,510 --> 00:42:36,710
Can you get used to it?

646
00:42:37,150 --> 00:42:37,800
Yes, I can.
